rdf:Description.rdfs:label: EternalHighPriest
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Whether the Jesus Christ, the Eternal High Priest, is celebrated in the current calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Locale
rdf:Description.skos:definition: IETF language codes comprehensive of region and optionally an ISO 15924 script code, following the BCP 47 standard as implemented in PHP intl

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Epiphany
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Enumeration that describes when Epiphany is celebrated in the current calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CalendarSettings
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the settings utilized (and possibly requested) to generate the current calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: holy_day_of_obligation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the property will only exist and will be true if the celebration is a Holy Day of Obligation, according to the calendar requested; otherwise the property will be absent

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: day
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the day of the month for the liturgical event, represented as an integer from 1 to 31 depending on the month

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: event_idx
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A sequential index number assigned to each liturgical event in the calendar, starting from 0 for the first event that is calculated. This index helps to uniquely identify and reference each event within the liturgical calendar for that year, seeing that the `event_key` property might not be unique.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LiturgicalEvent
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a liturgical event in the calendar, such as a solemnity, feast, memorial, temporal celebration, weekday etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsFerial
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the standard lectionary reading schema for ferial (weekday) Masses

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DiocesanCalendarSettings
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the settings that were utilized (and possibly requested) to generate the diocesan calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: NationalCalendarSettings
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the settings utilized (and possibly requested) to generate the national calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HolyDaysOfObligation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a map of `event_key`s to booleans, that indicate which of the standard holy days of obligation are observed in the current requested calendar, plus any additional holy days of obligation proper to the calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ConditionalRule
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a conditional rule that can be used to adjust dates of liturgical events based on certain conditions; an example is the National Day of Prayer for the Unborn in the United States

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsMultipleSchemas
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Used for All Souls Day (Commemoration of the Faithful Departed), which has three possible schemas for the three allowed Masses.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is_vigil_mass
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the property will only exist and will be true if the celebration is a Vigil Mass (i.e., the evening Mass on the day before a solemnity or sunday where the readings may be the same as those used on the day itself); otherwise the property will be absent

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: MissalDef
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration of Roman Missals supported by the Liturgical Calendar API

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsFestive
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the standard lectionary reading schema for festive (feast) Masses

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LiturgicalEventVigil
rdf:Description.skos:definition: When we say vigil, it is in the broad sense of the term, as in the evening Mass on the day preceding the main celebration, where the readings are often the same as those of the day of the main celebration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsEasterVigil
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the standard lectionary reading schema for the Easter Vigil Mass

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has_vesper_ii
rdf:Description.skos:definition: indicates whether the celebration has Second Vespers (the vespers of the evening of the day of the main celebration)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Readings
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the lectionary readings for the Mass associated with this liturgical event, following one of several possible schemas depending on the type of celebration

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsChristmas
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the standard lectionary reading schema for Christmas Masses (Night, Dawn, and Day); the evening vigil Mass is separated out into its own event

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: GeneralRomanCalendarSettings
rdf:Description.skos:definition: .the settings that were utilized (and possibly requested) to generate the General Roman Calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsSeasonal
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Lectionary readings that change depending on whether the liturgical event falls within the Easter season.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LitColor
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an array of enumeration values describing the liturgical color(s) associated with the celebration; if more than one liturgical common is associated with a celebration, there may be more than one color associated with the celebration

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Timezone
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a timezone identifier from the IANA Time Zone Database, useful for indicating the timezone for a diocesan calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: MissalID
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration of Roman Missal IDs for the Roman Missals supported by the Liturgical Calendar API

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsCommons
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Used for memorials and optional memorials that do not have a Proper lectionary. The readings are taken from the Common of Saints, or from Masses for Various Needs and Occasions, as appropriate. Indicates the name of the Common or Mass for Various Needs and Occasions from which the readings are taken.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is_vigil_for
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the `event_key` of the main celebration for which this vigil mass is being held

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsWithEvening
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Used for Easter Sunday, which has both a daytime and an evening Mass, each with proper readings.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: grade_display
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized string for display purposes that may differ from the standard name of the liturgical grade; can be null if no special display name is needed, or an empty string if no particular grade is meant to be shown. For example, for Higher Grade Solemnities it would be undesirable to display 'Solemnity with precedence over other solemnities', so this property would be an empty string in that case; or for All Souls Day which is logically treated as a Solemnity but displayed as a 'Commemoration' or as an 'Optional memorial' (according to local translations), so a localized string such as 'Commemoration' or 'Optional memorial' would be appropriate.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: grade_abbr
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized abbreviation for the liturgical grade of the celebration, such as 'S' for Solemnity, 'F' for Feast, 'M' for Memorial, etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Ascension
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Enumeration that describes when Ascension is celebrated in the current calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Nation
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration of ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes representing nations for which national liturgical calendars can be defined

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LitCommon
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an array of enumeration values describing the Liturgical Common(s), or Proper, or Masses for Various Needs and Occasions, of the celebration

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has_vesper_i
rdf:Description.skos:definition: indicates whether the celebration has First Vespers (the vespers of the evening prior to the main celebration)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: RelativeDateObject
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a relative date object, describing a day of the week relative to a liturgical event, useful for calculating moveable celebrations

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DiocesanCalendarId
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a unique identifier for a diocesan calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has_vigil_mass
rdf:Description.skos:definition: indicates whether the celebration has an associated Vigil Mass (i.e., the evening Mass on the day before the main celebration where the readings may be the same as those used on the day itself)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: common_lcl
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized string describing the liturgical Proper or common(s) (if any) associated with the celebration, according to the locale requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ReadingsPalmSunday
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the standard lectionary reading schema for Palm Sunday Masses

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: day_of_the_week_long
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized full string for the day of the week of the liturgical event, such as 'luned' for Monday if Italian was requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: month
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the month for the liturgical event, represented as an integer from 1 (January) to 12 (December)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: EventKey
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the `event_key` property of liturgical events in the output of the LitCal API and similar endpoints

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: settings
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Settings for the liturgical calendar request - can be one of GeneralRomanCalendarSettings, NationalCalendarSettings, or DiocesanCalendarSettings

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: month_long
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized full string for the month of the liturgical event, such as 'gennaio' for January if Italian was requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Day
rdf:Description.skos:definition: day of the month; the maximum value will be 28, 29, 30, or 31 depending on whether we are dealing with a leap year, and whether we are dealing with a month that usually has 28, 30, or 31 days

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Timestamp
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the earliest possible event timestamp corresponds to Nov 29th 1969, saturday vigil of the First Sunday of Advent

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the localized full name of the liturgical event in the locale requested and according to the current requested calendar (i.e. General Roman Calendar, National Calendar, Diocesan Calendar)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CorpusChristi
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Enumeration that describes when Corpus Christi is celebrated in the current calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metadata
rdf:Description.skos:definition: contains information about the current API version, how and when the current response was produced, and keys of liturgical events that can have precedence over others, useful for further calculations of a local calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: psalter_week
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the psalter week (1 to 4) for the liturgical event, used in the Liturgy of the Hours, if applicable; otherwise 0

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: liturgical_year
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized string representing the liturgical year designation (YEAR A, YEAR B, or YEAR C for Sundays and Solemnities; YEAR I or YEAR II for weekdays) according to the liturgical calendar cycle in use for the requested year

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: date
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the date of the liturgical event in ISO 8601 (RFC 3339) format, always at midnight UTC time

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DioceseName
rdf:Description.skos:definition: The full name of the Diocese for which a diocesan calendar has been defined / requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: WiderRegionCalendarAction
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration of supported actions that act upon a liturgical event in a Wider Region calendar definition

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: NationalCalendarAction
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration of supported actions that act upon a liturgical event in a National calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: NationalCalendarId
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a unique identifier for a national calendar

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: month_short
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized abbreviated string for the month of the liturgical event, such as 'gen.' for January if Italian was requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Missals
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Missals as defined in the PHP RomanMissal enum, from which data for the current calendar is drawn

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: EventKeyNonVigilMass
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the `event_key` property of the main celebration of a liturgical event in the output of the LitCal API and similar endpoints

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: day_of_the_week_iso8601
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the day of the week for the liturgical event, following the ISO 8601 standard where Monday is 1 and Sunday is 7

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LitEventType
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration value indicating whether the liturgical event is of type `fixed` or `mobile`

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: litcal
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Can be either a LiturgicalEvent or LiturgicalEventVigil

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: LitGrade
rdf:Description.skos:definition: 0 = WEEKDAY, 1 = COMMEMORATION, 2 = MEMORIAL_OPT, 3 = MEMORIAL, 4 = FEAST, 5 = FEAST_LORD, 6 = SOLEMNITY, 7 = HIGHER_SOLEMNITY

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: liturgical_season_lcl
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized string representing the name of the liturgical season in which the event falls, according to the locale requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: MissalName
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration of Roman Missal names for the Roman Missals supported by the Liturgical Calendar API

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DateTimeObjectCollection
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a collection of date-time objects representing liturgical events, such as the solemnities of the Lord and the Blessed Virgin Mary, solemnities, feasts of the Lord, feasts, memorials, suppressed events, or reinstated events

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: liturgical_season
rdf:Description.skos:definition: an enumeration value of the liturgical season in which the event falls, one of: ADVENT, CHRISTMAS, LENT, EASTER_TRIDUUM, EASTER, ORDINARY_TIME

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: day_of_the_week_short
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized abbreviated string for the day of the week of the liturgical event, such as 'lun.' for Monday if Italian was requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: grade_lcl
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a localized string describing the liturgical grade of the celebration, such as 'Solemnity', 'Feast', 'Memorial', etc., according to the locale requested

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Year
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the year for the liturgical event or for the current requested calendar, represented as a four-digit integer

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Month
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the month for the liturgical event, represented as an integer from 1 (January) to 12 (December)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: EventKeyVigilMass
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the `event_key` property of Vigil Mass liturgical events in the output of the LitCal API and similar endpoints; vigil is used in the broad sense, i.e., the evening Mass on the day before a solemnity or sunday where the readings may be the same as those used on the day itself
